EmailTemplate.name: DR 2015 - Final Email
EmailTemplate.subject: Live Different: Get Ready!
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Hello Live Different Build Volunteers,
Wow! Can you believe that in just a few short weeks you will be in the Dominican Republic? I hope you are all just as excited as we are for your trip. If you've been with us before, we're so glad to have you back. If this is your first time, we're so excited for you to learn, make friends and do great work with us!
We have some final information and reminders. (There is a lot of important information below. Please take the time to read it thoroughly!)
1. FLIGHTS When you land in Puerto Plata, our staff will be wearing a Live Different t-shirt or holding a Live Different sign. Come find us and we'll take you back to Sosua by the Sea where you can unpack and meet the group.
2. PASSPORTS
Please bring 2 photocopies of your passport with you. One will be given to staff, and the other is for you to keep on yourself. This is a precaution just in case your passport goes missing while travelling. Double check before you leave your driveway that you have your passport with you. You must have a valid passport to travel with us to Dominican Republic.
3. EXCURSIONS There will be an optional excursion on your day off! Activities will be explained and announced on your first night in Dominican Republic. The costs of the full day excursion is generally between $80-90 USD.
4. EMERGENCY CONTACTS If your family needs to contact you in case of emergency while in the Dominican Republic, these are the numbers to call: Live Different Build Office:1-866-432-4464 (toll free) Tara: 1 809 965 6943 Cole: 1 829 305 8198 Sousa by the Sea: 809-571-3222
For general inquiries and non-urgent matters, please contact us via email at jenn@livedifferent.com.
5. PHONE AND INTERNET ACCESS
Calling cards do not often work in the DR. Some past participants have put international plans on their cell phones prior to leaving but you will need to contact your cell service provider to see if this is possible. There is wifi available for purchase at the resort. Costs for this are $2 for an hour, $5 for a day, $25 for the week (USD). Some people like to bring their laptops as well, but keep in mind that Live Different is not responsible for lost or stolen items. There are safes available in the rooms for smaller valuable items, but they are not large enough to fit most laptops.
6. SPENDING MONEY/CURRENCY - It is best to bring cash in USD. Dominican Pesos are also accepted, but Canadian currency is not. - Please consider the following when deciding how much spending money to bring:
Your meals while traveling to and from your home to Puerto Plata Any personal spending (for things like souvenirs or snacks) $30 USD Resort staff tip - suggested amount $20 USD for a night out for dinner in a fun beach town with your team. $90 USD if you choose to participate in the day off excursion
7. PROJECT PAGE We have set up a project page which will be updated daily:
http://livedifferent.com/builds/dr-2015-summer-public-trip
On this trip page, under the "PROJECT" tab, your family and friends can see daily updates, links to the photos on our Live Different facebook page, and the trip blogs. Once your trip has started, feel free to tell your friends and family to check out this page. (Hint, if you email this link to them or post it on your facebook, it's a lot easier for them to find it!). We do our best to post a blog everyday but sometimes there are issues with the resort's internet. Also on the projects tab, you can read all about the families you will be building for! **This info will be posted online soon!**
8. PACKING LIST A packing list is attached for all who need it again. Don't forget to pack bug spray :)
9. YOUR LIVE DIFFERENT STAFF Peter, Tara, Liam and Cole will be your trip hosts. They're looking forward to meeting you all! (And seeing some familiar faces!)
Thank you for taking the time to read through all of that very important information. If you have any questions, please feel free to send me an email or give me a call in our office at 1 866 432 4464.
Have a great trip! Jenn Digiandomenico
